# Line-ending policy for cross-platform (Linux + Windows/MSYS2) checkouts.
#
# Without this, core.autocrlf=true on Windows converts text files to CRLF on
# checkout. That is fatal for the shell scripts: they run under MSYS2 /
# git-bash, and a non-interactive bash chokes on the trailing CR
# ("$'\r': command not found", "syntax error near unexpected token $'do\r'").
# Pin shell scripts to LF and the Windows scripts to CRLF so both work
# regardless of the cloning machine's autocrlf setting. Other file types are
# intentionally left to the existing autocrlf behaviour (no mass renormalise).

# Shell scripts MUST be LF (run by bash/sh under MSYS2 on Windows).
*.sh   text eol=lf

# Windows scripts stay CRLF.
*.bat  text eol=crlf
*.cmd  text eol=crlf
*.ps1  text eol=crlf
